         <packagedElement xmi:id="skos.XMLSchemaDataTypes"
                           xmi:uuid="https://example.org/cdifcodelist#XMLSchemaDataTypes"
                           xmi:type="uml:Package">
            <ownedComment xmi:id="skos.XMLSchemaDataTypes-ownedComment"
                           xmi:uuid="https://example.org/cdifcodelist#XMLSchemaDataTypes-ownedComment"
                           xmi:type="uml:Comment">
               <body>This package contains the datatypes as defined in the W3C XML Schema specifications (https://www.w3.org/XML/Schema).</body>
               <annotatedElement xmi:idref="skos.XMLSchemaDataTypes"/>
            </ownedComment>
            <name>XMLSchemaDataTypes</name>
            <packagedElement xmi:id="skos.XsdAnyUri"
                              xmi:uuid="https://example.org/cdifcodelist#XsdAnyUri"
                              xmi:type="uml:PrimitiveType">
               <ownedComment xmi:id="skos.XsdAnyUri-ownedComment"
                              xmi:uuid="https://example.org/cdifcodelist#XsdAnyUri-ownedComment"
                              xmi:type="uml:Comment">
                  <body>Definition
============
Primitive data type "anyURI" of the XML Schema data types.

Definition from XML Schema Part 2: Datatypes Second Edition:
"anyURI" represents a Uniform Resource Identifier Reference (URI). An "anyURI" value can be absolute or relative, and may have an optional fragment identifier (i.e., it may be a URI Reference). This type should be used to specify the intention that the value fulfills the role of a URI as defined by [RFC 2396], as amended by [RFC 2732]. For details see https://www.w3.org/TR/xmlschema-2/#anyURI.</body>
                  <annotatedElement xmi:idref="skos.XsdAnyUri"/>
               </ownedComment>
               <name>XsdAnyUri</name>
            </packagedElement>
            <packagedElement xmi:id="skos.XsdLanguage"
                              xmi:uuid="https://example.org/cdifcodelist#XsdLanguage"
                              xmi:type="uml:PrimitiveType">
               <ownedComment xmi:id="skos.XsdLanguage-ownedComment"
                              xmi:uuid="https://example.org/cdifcodelist#XsdLanguage-ownedComment"
                              xmi:type="uml:Comment">
                  <body>Definition
============
Derived data type "language" of the XML Schema data types.

Definition from XML Schema Part 2: Datatypes Second Edition:
"language" represents natural language identifiers as defined by by [RFC 3066]. The value space of "language" is the set of all strings that are valid language identifiers as defined [RFC 3066] . The lexical space of language is the set of all strings that conform to the pattern [a-zA-Z]{1,8}(-[a-zA-Z0-9]{1,8})*. The base type of "language" is token. https://www.w3.org/TR/xmlschema-2/#language.</body>
                  <annotatedElement xmi:idref="skos.XsdLanguage"/>
               </ownedComment>
               <name>XsdLanguage</name>
            </packagedElement>
         </packagedElement>
      </packagedElement>
   </uml:Model>
</xmi:XMI>
